Incomplete: Article 62 lists multiple Tier 2 items (a)-(d), but the Answer only mentions point (a).

Correct Answer:
According to Article 62, Tier 2 items consist of:

(a) capital instruments where the conditions set out in Article 63 are met, and to the extent specified in Article 64;

(b) the share premium accounts related to instruments referred to in point (a);

(c) for institutions calculating risk-weighted exposure amounts in accordance with Chapter 2 of Title II of Part Three, general credit risk adjustments, gross of tax effects, of up to 1.25% of those risk-weighted exposure amounts;

(d) for institutions calculating risk-weighted exposure amounts in accordance with Part Three, Title II, Chapter 3, the IRB excess, where applicable, gross of tax effects, of up to 0.6% of those risk-weighted exposure amounts.

case_020.note:
Answer should retrieve other relevant articles.

Recommended answer:

According to Article 71, the Tier 2 capital of an institution consists of its Tier 2 items after deductions referred to in Article 66 and after the application of Article 79.

Tier 2 items (Article 62) include:

(a) capital instruments where the conditions set out in Article 63 are met, and to the extent specified in Article 64;

(b) the share premium accounts related to those instruments;

(c) for institutions using Chapter 2 of Title II of Part Three, general credit risk adjustments, gross of tax effects, up to 1.25% of risk-weighted exposure amounts;

(d) for institutions using Part Three, Title II, Chapter 3, the IRB excess, where applicable, gross of tax effects, up to 0.6% of risk-weighted exposure amounts.

Deductions from Tier 2 items (Article 66) include:

(a) direct, indirect and synthetic holdings of own Tier 2 instruments;

(b) holdings of Tier 2 instruments of financial sector entities with reciprocal cross holdings;

(c) applicable amounts of holdings in Tier 2 instruments of financial sector entities without significant investment;

(d) holdings of Tier 2 instruments of financial sector entities with significant investment (excluding certain underwriting positions);

(e) amounts required to be deducted from eligible liabilities items that exceed those items.

Application of Article 79:

Competent authorities may temporarily waive deductions where holdings are for the purpose of financial assistance to restore viability of an entity.
